                            <comment id="14343818" author="apachespark" created="Mon, 2 Mar 2015 21:44:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;squito&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/4857&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/4857&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16074392" author="eyalfa" created="Wed, 5 Jul 2017 08:06:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just hit this with spark 2.1 when processing a disk persisted RDD&lt;br/&gt;
while the root cause for this is probably data skew, this seems like a severe limitation on spark.&lt;br/&gt;
this specific failure is a bit surprising as spark already knows the block size on disk at this point (it maps the entire file from offset 0 to file size), so it should easily be possible to split this into several blocks, after all the code is using ChunkedByteBuffer.&lt;br/&gt;
a better approach would be lazily loading the blocks as deserialization progresses , and an even better solution (proposed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=matei&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;matei&quot;&gt;matei&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-1476?focusedCommentId=13967947&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-13967947&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;comment&lt;/a&gt; for #1476) would be splitting these block in higher levels of spark (a mapper that produces multiple blocks, cached RDD partition that consists of several blocks...)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can see the attached PR is closed, is there an expected/in-progress fix for this?&lt;/p&gt;


